some coded phrases, "VIO" and "VIC". The British veterinary diagnostic
laboratories are known as "Veterinary Investigation Centres" and thus the
head of such a laboratory was known as the "Veterinary Investigation
Officer". I apologise for this presumption of arcane knowledge. I would
point out that they did investigate livestock problems on the farms in their
areas and were not passive diagnosticians. - Mod.MHJ
